<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Imgur Gallery</title><link>https://imgur.com</link><description>description</description><lastBuildDate>2024-02-16 05:10:50.764248</lastBuildDate><item><title>Absolutely perfect!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Oq2ttlt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eZxee8l.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I can confirm that last part works, at least with my kids it does. When my daughter was 16 we had moved so in her new school she made new friends. I agreed she could go and have a sleepover in a friends house... About midnight I got a phone call, they had been drinking and it was her first time being drunk, she hated it and thought she 'was dying' (I think most of us have been there lol) she just wanted me to come and get her... When I got there all her friends thought she'd be in trouble, they were shocked when I said absolutely not because she rang me, I explained she'd have been in big trouble if I found out the next day and she hadn't told me, that then the trust would be broken. It worked, the hangover was punishment enough any way because still now, 6 yrs later she hates getting drunk and doesn't let herself get that far! 

So talk to your kids, let them know that they can trust you and that trust goes both ways, always make sure they know they can reach out when they're in a bad situation, whatever that may be!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Oq2ttlt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DumpingSh1tandBeingKind2]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The neighbors look chill</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/iwq25Ei</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eggDm3E.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/iwq25Ei</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[DOcelot]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Troll move, or no big deal?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/sedHqHt</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WX8wRcg.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Nx0RBwH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/et2hh4i.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FalEzGO.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/sedHqHt</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[trustfallaccident]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>That’s not a photobomb, Sharknado is true!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/w2pIYab</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MS9LxMx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/w2pIYab</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PineappleIsDeliciousOnPizzaFightMe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>It's simple</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/P0YlOTK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/6tbfQaq.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></